<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
Four isolates clustered in a clade distinct from further 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Diaporthe</taxonomicName>
species based on DNA sequence data. Morphologically, this species is characterised by conical conidiomata, which is similar with 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. rostrata" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="rostrata">D. rostrata</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" genus="Juglans" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Juglans mandshurica" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mandshurica">Juglans mandshurica</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. conica" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="conica">D. conica</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. rostrata" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="rostrata">D. rostrata</taxonomicName>
by having smaller locule and alpha conidia (310-385 vs. 620-1100 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in locule; 5.5-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.3-3 vs. 8.5-11.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in alpha conidia) (
<bibRefCitation author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Mycological Progress" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" pagination="1 - 8" title="Diaportherostrata, a novel ascomycete from Juglansmandshurica associated with walnut dieback." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11557-015-1104-5" volume="14" year="2015">Fan et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
